{"questionListItems":[{"id":"clq62iz73008213sh4wy0wdwc","title":"Which flexible benefit is taxable, which is not?","body":"","createdAt":"2023-12-15T03:27:08.463Z","published":true,"publishedAt":"2023-12-15T03:27:08.637Z","priority":0,"answer":{"id":"clq62iz96008313shfiq1myym","body":"<p>Generally, all gains and profits derived by an employee due to his employment are taxable. Benefits are \"gains and profits\" and are taxable unless exempted or given an <a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" href=\"https://www.iras.gov.sg/taxes/individual-income-tax/employers/understanding-the-tax-treatment/list-of-benefits-in-kind-granted-administrative-concession-or-exempt-from-income-tax\">administrative concession</a>.</p><br><p>An employer offering the flexible benefits scheme would have to make a distinction between taxable and non-taxable benefits. The employer has to keep track of the taxable items so that the taxable benefits are reported in the <a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" href=\"https://www.iras.gov.sg/docs/default-source/individual-income-tax/employers/form-ir8a.doc?sfvrsn=d6cdd41_6\">Form IR8A</a>.</p>","updatedAt":"2023-12-15T03:27:08.538Z","numPositiveFeedback":0},"topics":[{"id":781,"title":"Individual Income Tax","priority":0,"agencyId":"cln4erax3001e5j0x1hjah8bj","parentTopicId":null,"parentTopic":null}],"agency":{"code":"iras","logoUrl":"https://logos.ask.gov.sg/IRAS.png"}},{"id":"clq62gh07000813shraexrvp6","title":"How do I declare other income or make changes to the relief claim that has been pre-filled in my Income, Deduction and Reliefs Statement?","body":null,"createdAt":"2023-12-15T03:25:11.571Z","published":true,"publishedAt":"2023-12-15T03:25:11.511Z","priority":0,"answer":{"id":"clq62gh07000913shdii2xgp0","body":"<p>To make changes, you need to file your 2024 tax return via <a class=\"eyd-external-link\" data-sf-ec-immutable=\"\" href=\"https://mytax.iras.gov.sg/ESVWeb/default.aspx\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"myTax Portal\">myTax Portal</a> from 1 Mar to 18 Apr. Visit <a href=\"https://www.iras.gov.sg/taxes/individual-income-tax/basics-of-individual-income-tax/understanding-my-income-tax-filing/e-filing-your-income-tax-return\" title=\"e-Filing your Income Tax Return\">Tips on e-Filing</a> for more details on how to proceed.</p><p>Please check that you have met the <a href=\"https://www.iras.gov.sg/taxes/individual-income-tax/basics-of-individual-income-tax/tax-reliefs-rebates-and-deductions\" title=\"qualifying conditions\">qualifying conditions</a> for the respective tax reliefs before changing the relief claim. Alternatively, you may use the <a href=\"https://www.iras.gov.sg/taxes/individual-income-tax/basics-of-individual-income-tax/tax-reliefs-rebates-and-deductions/tax-reliefs\" title=\"Personal Relief Checker\">Relief Checker</a> and <a data-sf-ec-document-immutable=\"true\" data-sf-ec-immutable=\"\" href=\"https://www.iras.gov.sg/docs/default-source/individual-income-tax/employees/ptr-calculator.xlsm?sfvrsn=e185c04f_5\n\" title=\"PTR Eligibility Tool\">Parenthood Tax Rebate Eligibility Tool</a> (XLSM, 52KB). Please note that a <a data-sf-ec-immutable=\"\" href=\"https://www.iras.gov.sg/taxes/individual-income-tax/basics-of-individual-income-tax/tax-reliefs-rebates-and-deductions/tax-reliefs#title1\" title=\"personal income tax relief cap\">personal income tax relief cap</a> of $80,000 applies to the total amount of all tax reliefs claimed for each Year of Assessment.</p>","updatedAt":"2024-03-03T23:04:56.401Z","numPositiveFeedback":0},"topics":[{"id":781,"title":"Individual Income Tax","priority":0,"agencyId":"cln4erax3001e5j0x1hjah8bj","parentTopicId":null,"parentTopic":null},{"id":794,"title":"General tax matters (for Singapore Citizens or PRs)","priority":0,"agencyId":"cln4erax3001e5j0x1hjah8bj","parentTopicId":781,"parentTopic":{"title":"Individual Income Tax"}}],"agency":{"code":"iras","logoUrl":"https://logos.ask.gov.sg/IRAS.png"}},{"id":"clq62gh07000a13shljtgg0tk","title":"I have filed my tax return and overlooked to claim a tax relief. What should I do?","body":null,"createdAt":"2023-12-15T03:25:11.571Z","published":true,"publishedAt":"2023-12-15T03:25:11.511Z","priority":0,"answer":{"id":"clq62gh07000b13sh2qb6rdgm","body":"<p>Please check that you have met the <a href=\"https://www.iras.gov.sg/taxes/individual-income-tax/basics-of-individual-income-tax/tax-reliefs-rebates-and-deductions/tax-reliefs\" title=\"qualifying conditions\">qualifying conditions</a> for the respective tax reliefs. Thereafter, re-file your tax return at <a class=\"eyd-external-link\" data-sf-ec-immutable=\"\" href=\"https://mytax.iras.gov.sg/ESVWeb/default.aspx\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"myTax Portal\">myTax Portal</a> and include your tax relief claim. Re-filing is available only once within 7 days of your previous submission or by 18 Apr, whichever is earlier.</p><p>If you are unable to re-file, email us via <a class=\"eyd-external-link\" data-sf-ec-immutable=\"\" href=\"https://mytax.iras.gov.sg/ESVWeb/default.aspx?target=MTAXMMain&amp;toLoginSelection=true\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"myTax Mail\">myTax Mail</a> with the details of your claim.</p>","updatedAt":"2023-12-15T03:25:11.571Z","numPositiveFeedback":0},"topics":[{"id":781,"title":"Individual Income Tax","priority":0,"agencyId":"cln4erax3001e5j0x1hjah8bj","parentTopicId":null,"parentTopic":null},{"id":794,"title":"General tax matters (for Singapore Citizens or PRs)","priority":0,"agencyId":"cln4erax3001e5j0x1hjah8bj","parentTopicId":781,"parentTopic":{"title":"Individual Income Tax"}}],"agency":{"code":"iras","logoUrl":"https://logos.ask.gov.sg/IRAS.png"}},{"id":"clq62gh07000e13sh1gqnw5zn","title":"I am on GIRO. Why is IRAS deducting from my bank account when I have not received my tax bill for this year?","body":null,"createdAt":"2023-12-15T03:25:11.571Z","published":true,"publishedAt":"2023-12-15T03:25:11.511Z","priority":0,"answer":{"id":"clq62gh07000f13sh05kqyexp","body":"<p>Once you are on GIRO payment scheme, your instalments will continue in May each year to April of the following year, based on a Provisional Instalment Plan (PIP).</p><p>The PIP allows you to enjoy the maximum 12 months instalment. Your PIP will be revised when your tax assessment for the year is finalised subsequently. The tax instalments that you have paid will be used to offset your actual tax assessed and the instalments for the remaining months will be adjusted accordingly.</p><p>Excess payment, if any, will be automatically refunded to you. There is no need for you to make a claim for refund.</p>","updatedAt":"2023-12-15T03:25:11.571Z","numPositiveFeedback":0},"topics":[{"id":781,"title":"Individual Income Tax","priority":0,"agencyId":"cln4erax3001e5j0x1hjah8bj","parentTopicId":null,"parentTopic":null},{"id":794,"title":"General tax matters (for Singapore Citizens or PRs)","priority":0,"agencyId":"cln4erax3001e5j0x1hjah8bj","parentTopicId":781,"parentTopic":{"title":"Individual Income Tax"}}],"agency":{"code":"iras","logoUrl":"https://logos.ask.gov.sg/IRAS.png"}},{"id":"clq62gh07000g13shc7ji5pr6","title":"How can I request for a longer payment plan to pay my tax?","body":null,"createdAt":"2023-12-15T03:25:11.571Z","published":true,"publishedAt":"2023-12-15T03:25:11.511Z","priority":0,"answer":{"id":"clq62gh07000h13sh3oc8z3ra","body":"<p>IRAS will only grant instalments by GIRO. You may appeal for a longer payment plan via the ‘Apply for Payment Plan’ digital service at <a class=\"eyd-external-link\" data-sf-ec-immutable=\"\" href=\"https://mytax.iras.gov.sg/ESVWeb/default.aspx\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"myTax Portal\">myTax Portal</a> using your Singpass. Visit <a href=\"https://www.iras.gov.sg/taxes/individual-income-tax/basics-of-individual-income-tax/receive-tax-bill-pay-tax-check-refunds/experiencing-difficulties-in-paying-your-tax\" title=\"Experiencing Difficulties in Paying Your Tax\">Experiencing Difficulties in Paying Your Tax</a> for more details.</p><p>If you have an existing GIRO arrangement, you may appeal for longer instalment plan via the <a class=\"eyd-external-link\" data-sf-ec-immutable=\"\" href=\"https://mytax.iras.gov.sg/ESVWeb/default.aspx?target=MPYMApplyGIROBankDetails&amp;toLoginSelection=true\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Apply for Payment Plan\">Apply for Payment Plan</a> digital service.</p><p>If you do not have an existing GIRO arrangement, please refer to the guide at <a href=\"https://www.iras.gov.sg/digital-services/employees\" title=\"Digital Services\">Apply for Payment Plan</a> for the detailed steps to appeal for longer instalment plan.</p>","updatedAt":"2023-12-15T03:25:11.571Z","numPositiveFeedback":0},"topics":[{"id":781,"title":"Individual Income Tax","priority":0,"agencyId":"cln4erax3001e5j0x1hjah8bj","parentTopicId":null,"parentTopic":null},{"id":794,"title":"General tax matters (for Singapore Citizens or PRs)","priority":0,"agencyId":"cln4erax3001e5j0x1hjah8bj","parentTopicId":781,"parentTopic":{"title":"Individual Income Tax"}}],"agency":{"code":"iras","logoUrl":"https://logos.ask.gov.sg/IRAS.png"}},{"id":"clq62gh07000i13shuemisbjt","title":"What should I do if the employment income information transmitted by my employer shown in my Income, Deduction and Reliefs Statement is wrong?","body":null,"createdAt":"2023-12-15T03:25:11.571Z","published":true,"publishedAt":"2023-12-15T03:25:11.511Z","priority":0,"answer":{"id":"clq62gh07000j13sh3mbn27fy","body":"<p>You will not be able to make changes to the employment information transmitted by your employer. Do inform your employer and they will work with IRAS to amend the information.</p>","updatedAt":"2023-12-15T03:25:11.571Z","numPositiveFeedback":0},"topics":[{"id":781,"title":"Individual Income Tax","priority":0,"agencyId":"cln4erax3001e5j0x1hjah8bj","parentTopicId":null,"parentTopic":null},{"id":794,"title":"General tax matters (for Singapore Citizens or PRs)","priority":0,"agencyId":"cln4erax3001e5j0x1hjah8bj","parentTopicId":781,"parentTopic":{"title":"Individual Income Tax"}}],"agency":{"code":"iras","logoUrl":"https://logos.ask.gov.sg/IRAS.png"}},{"id":"clq62gh07000k13shzy9lc230","title":"Must I file a tax return since my employer has transmitted my employment income details to IRAS?","body":null,"createdAt":"2023-12-15T03:25:11.571Z","published":true,"publishedAt":"2023-12-15T03:25:11.511Z","priority":0,"answer":{"id":"clq62gh08000l13shrkyt1bgc","body":"<p>Although your employer has transmitted your employment income details to IRAS, you are still required to e-File your Income Tax Return unless you have received the No-Filing Service (NFS) letter/SMS or your filing status is “Processed”. You may refer to <a href=\"https://www.iras.gov.sg/taxes/individual-income-tax/employers/auto-inclusion-scheme-(ais)-for-employment-income/inform-employees-to-file-tax-returns\">this link</a> for more details.</p>","updatedAt":"2023-12-15T03:25:11.571Z","numPositiveFeedback":0},"topics":[{"id":781,"title":"Individual Income Tax","priority":0,"agencyId":"cln4erax3001e5j0x1hjah8bj","parentTopicId":null,"parentTopic":null},{"id":793,"title":"General tax matters (for Foreigner)","priority":0,"agencyId":"cln4erax3001e5j0x1hjah8bj","parentTopicId":781,"parentTopic":{"title":"Individual Income Tax"}}],"agency":{"code":"iras","logoUrl":"https://logos.ask.gov.sg/IRAS.png"}},{"id":"clq62gh08000o13shinhf9val","title":"I received NFS SMS. How do I claim reliefs for my spouse and children?","body":null,"createdAt":"2023-12-15T03:25:11.571Z","published":true,"publishedAt":"2023-12-15T03:25:11.511Z","priority":0,"answer":{"id":"clq62gh08000p13shhk876rv7","body":"<p>To claim for reliefs, you need to file your 2024 tax return via <a class=\"eyd-external-link\" data-sf-ec-immutable=\"\" href=\"https://mytax.iras.gov.sg/ESVWeb/default.aspx\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"myTax Portal\">myTax Portal</a> from 1 Mar to 18 Apr. Visit <a href=\"https://www.iras.gov.sg/taxes/individual-income-tax/basics-of-individual-income-tax/understanding-my-income-tax-filing/e-filing-your-income-tax-return\" title=\"e-Filing your Income Tax Return\">Tips on e-Filing</a> for more details on how to proceed.</p><p>Please check that you have met the <a href=\"https://www.iras.gov.sg/taxes/individual-income-tax/basics-of-individual-income-tax/tax-reliefs-rebates-and-deductions\" title=\"qualifying conditions\">qualifying conditions</a> for the respective tax reliefs before changing the relief claim. Alternatively, you may use the <a href=\"https://www.iras.gov.sg/taxes/individual-income-tax/basics-of-individual-income-tax/tax-reliefs-rebates-and-deductions/tax-reliefs\" title=\"Personal Relief Checker\">Relief Checker</a>.</p>","updatedAt":"2024-03-03T23:04:56.401Z","numPositiveFeedback":0},"topics":[{"id":781,"title":"Individual Income Tax","priority":0,"agencyId":"cln4erax3001e5j0x1hjah8bj","parentTopicId":null,"parentTopic":null},{"id":793,"title":"General tax matters (for Foreigner)","priority":0,"agencyId":"cln4erax3001e5j0x1hjah8bj","parentTopicId":781,"parentTopic":{"title":"Individual Income Tax"}}],"agency":{"code":"iras","logoUrl":"https://logos.ask.gov.sg/IRAS.png"}},{"id":"clq62gh08000q13shxzokfaj3","title":"I did not receive my Singpass password as I have changed my address. What should I do?","body":null,"createdAt":"2023-12-15T03:25:11.571Z","published":true,"publishedAt":"2023-12-15T03:25:11.511Z","priority":0,"answer":{"id":"clq62gh08000r13shwn5t78xo","body":"<p>The Singpass PIN will be sent to your registered address maintained by the Ministry of Manpower (MOM). You or your employer need to login to EP Online to update the address. Your employer can make the change on your behalf. After that, you can request for a new Singpass mailer to be sent to you. Visit <a class=\"eyd-external-link\" data-sf-ec-immutable=\"\" href=\"https://www.singpass.gov.sg/home/ui/login\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Singpass Portal\">Singpass Portal</a> &gt; Select 'Services' on the top scroll bar &gt; Select 'Reset password'. Enter your 'FIN number' and 'Date of issue'.</p><p>For enquiries on filing of income tax, please visit <a href=\"https://www.iras.gov.sg/taxes/individual-income-tax/basics-of-individual-income-tax/understanding-my-income-tax-filing/tax-season-2024---all-you-need-to-know\" title=\"Tax Season 2023 - All you need to know\"></a><a href=\"https://www.iras.gov.sg/taxes/individual-income-tax/basics-of-individual-income-tax/understanding-my-income-tax-filing/tax-season-2024---all-you-need-to-know\">Tax Season 2024 – All you need to know</a></p><p>For enquiries on assessment, please visit <a href=\"https://www.iras.gov.sg/taxes/individual-income-tax/basics-of-individual-income-tax/understanding-my-income-tax-filing/tax-season-2024---about-your-tax-bill\" title=\"Tax Season 2023 - About Your Tax Bill\"></a><a href=\"https://www.iras.gov.sg/taxes/individual-income-tax/basics-of-individual-income-tax/understanding-my-income-tax-filing/tax-season-2024---about-your-tax-bill\">Tax Season 2024 – About Your Tax Bill</a></p><p>If your enquiry is regarding your personal tax matters, email us via <a class=\"eyd-external-link\" data-renderer-mark=\"true\" data-sf-ec-immutable=\"\" data-sf-marked=\"\" href=\"https://mytax.iras.gov.sg/ESVWeb/default.aspx\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"myTax Mail\">myTax Mail</a> with your <a class=\"eyd-external-link\" data-renderer-mark=\"true\" data-sf-ec-immutable=\"\" data-sf-marked=\"\" href=\"https://www.singpass.gov.sg/main/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Singpass\">Singpass</a> or <a href=\"https://www.iras.gov.sg/digital-services/others/singpass-foreign-user-account-(sfa)-for-foreign-individuals\" title=\"SFA\">Singpass Foreign user Account (SFA)</a>.</p>","updatedAt":"2024-03-03T23:04:56.401Z","numPositiveFeedback":0},"topics":[{"id":781,"title":"Individual Income Tax","priority":0,"agencyId":"cln4erax3001e5j0x1hjah8bj","parentTopicId":null,"parentTopic":null},{"id":793,"title":"General tax matters (for Foreigner)","priority":0,"agencyId":"cln4erax3001e5j0x1hjah8bj","parentTopicId":781,"parentTopic":{"title":"Individual Income Tax"}}],"agency":{"code":"iras","logoUrl":"https://logos.ask.gov.sg/IRAS.png"}},{"id":"clq62gh08000s13shxl58mmed","title":"What should I do if the employment income information transmitted by my employer shown in my Income, Deduction and Reliefs Statement is wrong?","body":null,"createdAt":"2023-12-15T03:25:11.571Z","published":true,"publishedAt":"2023-12-15T03:25:11.511Z","priority":0,"answer":{"id":"clq62gh08000t13shlog8lztz","body":"<p>You will not be able to make changes to the employment information transmitted by your employer. Do inform your employer and they will work with IRAS to amend the information.</p>","updatedAt":"2023-12-15T03:25:11.571Z","numPositiveFeedback":0},"topics":[{"id":781,"title":"Individual Income Tax","priority":0,"agencyId":"cln4erax3001e5j0x1hjah8bj","parentTopicId":null,"parentTopic":null},{"id":793,"title":"General tax matters (for Foreigner)","priority":0,"agencyId":"cln4erax3001e5j0x1hjah8bj","parentTopicId":781,"parentTopic":{"title":"Individual Income Tax"}}],"agency":{"code":"iras","logoUrl":"https://logos.ask.gov.sg/IRAS.png"}},{"id":"clq62gh08000u13shvazdp1s2","title":"I have filed my tax return and overlooked to claim a tax relief. What should I do?","body":null,"createdAt":"2023-12-15T03:25:11.571Z","published":true,"publishedAt":"2023-12-15T03:25:11.511Z","priority":0,"answer":{"id":"clq62gh08000v13sh0efgkywj","body":"<p>Please check that you have met the <a href=\"https://www.iras.gov.sg/taxes/individual-income-tax/basics-of-individual-income-tax/tax-reliefs-rebates-and-deductions/tax-reliefs\" title=\"qualifying conditions\">qualifying conditions</a> for the respective tax reliefs. Thereafter, re-file your tax return at <a class=\"eyd-external-link\" data-sf-ec-immutable=\"\" href=\"https://mytax.iras.gov.sg/ESVWeb/default.aspx\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"myTax Portal\">myTax Portal</a> and include your tax relief claim. Re-filing is available only once within 7 days of your previous submission or by 18 Apr, whichever is earlier.</p><p>If you are unable to re-file, email us via <a class=\"eyd-external-link\" data-sf-ec-immutable=\"\" href=\"https://mytax.iras.gov.sg/ESVWeb/default.aspx?target=MTAXMMain&amp;toLoginSelection=true\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"myTax Mail\">myTax Mail</a> with the details of your claim.</p>","updatedAt":"2023-12-15T03:25:11.571Z","numPositiveFeedback":0},"topics":[{"id":781,"title":"Individual Income Tax","priority":0,"agencyId":"cln4erax3001e5j0x1hjah8bj","parentTopicId":null,"parentTopic":null},{"id":793,"title":"General tax matters (for Foreigner)","priority":0,"agencyId":"cln4erax3001e5j0x1hjah8bj","parentTopicId":781,"parentTopic":{"title":"Individual Income Tax"}}],"agency":{"code":"iras","logoUrl":"https://logos.ask.gov.sg/IRAS.png"}},{"id":"clq62gh08000w13shk5k5zzwu","title":"What is the Not Ordinarily Resident (NOR) scheme? Do I qualify for the scheme?","body":null,"createdAt":"2023-12-15T03:25:11.571Z","published":true,"publishedAt":"2023-12-15T03:25:11.511Z","priority":0,"answer":{"id":"clq62gh08000x13sh2eqeje96","body":"<p>Find out more about the <a href=\"https://www.iras.gov.sg/taxes/individual-income-tax/basics-of-individual-income-tax/special-tax-schemes/not-ordinarily-resident-(nor)-scheme\" title=\"NOR scheme\">NOR scheme</a> and the tax concessions. You can use the <a data-sf-ec-document-immutable=\"true\" href=\"https://www.iras.gov.sg/media/docs/default-source/uploadedfiles/xls/nor-status-calculator-2.xls?sfvrsn=610cc1be_4\" title=\"NOR status calculator\">NOR status calculator</a> (XLS, 89KB) to check whether you are eligible for the scheme.</p>","updatedAt":"2023-12-15T03:25:11.571Z","numPositiveFeedback":0},"topics":[{"id":781,"title":"Individual Income Tax","priority":0,"agencyId":"cln4erax3001e5j0x1hjah8bj","parentTopicId":null,"parentTopic":null},{"id":792,"title":"General tax matters (for NOR or those with foreign employer)","priority":0,"agencyId":"cln4erax3001e5j0x1hjah8bj","parentTopicId":781,"parentTopic":{"title":"Individual Income Tax"}}],"agency":{"code":"iras","logoUrl":"https://logos.ask.gov.sg/IRAS.png"}},{"id":"clq62gh08000y13shzhq74wzn","title":"What is the filing due date for applying for the NOR scheme?","body":null,"createdAt":"2023-12-15T03:25:11.571Z","published":true,"publishedAt":"2023-12-15T03:25:11.511Z","priority":0,"answer":{"id":"clq62gh08000z13sh3pghmtoi","body":"<p>You must submit the <a data-sf-ec-document-immutable=\"true\" href=\"https://www.iras.gov.sg/media/docs/default-source/uploadedfiles/doc/application-for-not-ordinarily-resident-(nor-scheme)-2.doc?sfvrsn=12e9dff4_11\" title=\"Application for Not Ordinarily Resident (NOR Scheme)\">Application for Not Ordinarily Resident (NOR Scheme)</a> (DOC, 362KB) by 15 Apr of the Year of Assessment (YA) for which the NOR tax concessions are applied. If you e-File your tax return, please submit the application form by 18 Apr of that YA.</p>","updatedAt":"2024-01-07T23:08:14.840Z","numPositiveFeedback":0},"topics":[{"id":781,"title":"Individual Income Tax","priority":0,"agencyId":"cln4erax3001e5j0x1hjah8bj","parentTopicId":null,"parentTopic":null},{"id":792,"title":"General tax matters (for NOR or those with foreign employer)","priority":0,"agencyId":"cln4erax3001e5j0x1hjah8bj","parentTopicId":781,"parentTopic":{"title":"Individual Income Tax"}}],"agency":{"code":"iras","logoUrl":"https://logos.ask.gov.sg/IRAS.png"}},{"id":"clq62gh08001013sh9jraavpc","title":"My employer is an overseas company. Am I considered to be working for a foreign employer?","body":null,"createdAt":"2023-12-15T03:25:11.571Z","published":true,"publishedAt":"2023-12-15T03:25:11.511Z","priority":0,"answer":{"id":"clq62gh08001113sh9y43m4yw","body":"<p>Find out more on <a href=\"https://www.iras.gov.sg/taxes/individual-income-tax/employees/scenario-based-faqs-for-working-in-singapore-and-abroad/i-am-working-for-a-foreign-employer\" title=\"working for foreign employers\">working for foreign employers</a>. However, you are not considered to be working for a foreign employer if:</p>","updatedAt":"2023-12-15T03:25:11.571Z","numPositiveFeedback":0},"topics":[{"id":781,"title":"Individual Income Tax","priority":0,"agencyId":"cln4erax3001e5j0x1hjah8bj","parentTopicId":null,"parentTopic":null},{"id":792,"title":"General tax matters (for NOR or those with foreign employer)","priority":0,"agencyId":"cln4erax3001e5j0x1hjah8bj","parentTopicId":781,"parentTopic":{"title":"Individual Income Tax"}}],"agency":{"code":"iras","logoUrl":"https://logos.ask.gov.sg/IRAS.png"}},{"id":"clq62gh08001413shfmru37j4","title":"I am based outside Singapore and travel into Singapore for business purpose. Am I liable to Singapore income tax if I am paying taxes in my home country/region?","body":null,"createdAt":"2023-12-15T03:25:11.571Z","published":true,"publishedAt":"2023-12-15T03:25:11.511Z","priority":0,"answer":{"id":"clq62gh08001513sh0i9xpd0r","body":"<p>If you are a tax resident of a jurisdiction that has a <a href=\"https://www.iras.gov.sg/taxes/international-tax/list-of-dtas-limited-dtas-and-eoi-arrangements\">DTA</a> with Singapore, it may protect you from being taxed twice on the same income. This depends on the provisions of the  DTA. Find out more about <a href=\"https://www.iras.gov.sg/media/docs/default-source/uploadedfiles/xls/tax-treaty-calculator-for-personal-services-rendered-by-employees2773e41e-6800-439e-ada2-c0c41cebc87b.xls?sfvrsn=222cd9cd_32\" title=\"DTA Calculator - Dependent Services\">DTA Calculator - Dependent Services</a> (XLS, 272KB). </p>","updatedAt":"2023-12-15T03:25:11.571Z","numPositiveFeedback":0},"topics":[{"id":781,"title":"Individ